Dialogue: 2,0:00:00.58,0:00:01.47,YYeTS-ENG,,0,0,0,,number three
Dialogue: 2,0:00:01.54,0:00:02.82,YYeTS-ENG,,0,0,0,,the Phillips curve
Dialogue: 2,0:00:03.25,0:00:07.09,YYeTS-ENG,,0,0,0,,bill Phillips was a crocodile and economist from new Zealand
Dialogue: 2,0:00:07.09,0:00:09.72,YYeTS-ENG,,0,0,0,,who spotted that when employment levels are high
Dialogue: 2,0:00:09.74,0:00:11.32,YYeTS-ENG,,0,0,0,,wages rise faster
Dialogue: 2,0:00:11.32,0:00:12.94,YYeTS-ENG,,0,0,0,,people have more money to spend 
Dialogue: 2,0:00:12.94,0:00:15.29,YYeTS-ENG,,0,0,0,,so prices go up and so does inflation
Dialogue: 2,0:00:15.29,0:00:17.30,YYeTS-ENG,,0,0,0,,likewise when unemployment is high 
Dialogue: 2,0:00:17.30,0:00:18.72,YYeTS-ENG,,0,0,0,,the lack of money to spend
Dialogue: 2,0:00:18.72,0:00:20.52,YYeTS-ENG,,0,0,0,,means inflation goes down
Dialogue: 2,0:00:20.94,0:00:23.21,YYeTS-ENG,,0,0,0,,this became known as the Phillips curve
Dialogue: 2,0:00:23.42,0:00:25.52,YYeTS-ENG,,0,0,0,,governments even set policy by the curve
Dialogue: 2,0:00:25.72,0:00:26.59,YYeTS-ENG,,0,0,0,,tolerating the inflation 
Dialogue: 2,0:00:26.59,0:00:28.68,YYeTS-ENG,,0,0,0,,when they spent extra money creating jobs
Dialogue: 2,0:00:29.25,0:00:30.07,YYeTS-ENG,,0,0,0,,but they forgot that the 
Dialogue: 2,0:00:30.07,0:00:32.57,YYeTS-ENG,,0,0,0,,workers could also see the effects of the curve 
Dialogue: 2,0:00:32.57,0:00:34.63,YYeTS-ENG,,0,0,0,,so when unemployment went down
Dialogue: 2,0:00:34.63,0:00:36.15,YYeTS-ENG,,0,0,0,,they spected inflation
Dialogue: 2,0:00:36.15,0:00:37.85,YYeTS-ENG,,0,0,0,,and demanded higher wages causing
Dialogue: 2,0:00:37.85,0:00:39.38,YYeTS-ENG,,0,0,0,, unemployment to go back up
Dialogue: 2,0:00:39.42,0:00:41.19,YYeTS-ENG,,0,0,0,,while inflation remained high
Dialogue: 2,0:00:41.19,0:00:43.38,YYeTS-ENG,,0,0,0,,which is what happened in the 1970s
Dialogue: 2,0:00:43.38,0:00:46.05,YYeTS-ENG,,0,0,0,,when both inflation and unemployment rose
Dialogue: 2,0:00:46.42,0:00:47.54,YYeTS-ENG,,0,0,0,,then in the 1990s
Dialogue: 2,0:00:47.57,0:00:50.39,YYeTS-ENG,,0,0,0,,unemployment dropped while inflation stayed low
Dialogue: 2,0:00:50.54,0:00:53.57,YYeTS-ENG,,0,0,0,,which old Robert took the band out of phillips's curve
Dialogue: 2,0:00:53.57,0:00:56.66,YYeTS-ENG,,0,0,0,,but at least part of Philips troubles and tradeoff lives on
Dialogue: 2,0:00:56.84,0:00:59.50,YYeTS-ENG,,0,0,0,,when foster growth and full employment return
Dialogue: 2,0:00:59.64,0:01:02.78,YYeTS-ENG,,0,0,0,,you can bet inflation will be along to spoil the party